            <td><p>I am a recent PhD from the <a href="http://www.stat.umn.edu/"> School of Statistics of the
                  University of Minnesota</a>.  My advisor is Prof. <a href="http://users.stat.umn.edu/~chatt019/">Anshu Chatterjee</a>,
                  and I work on inferential problems based on statistical depth functions, focusing on robust dimension reduction and variable selection.
                </p>
                <p>
                  I am passionate about substantial applications of cutting-edge statistical methodologies in real life problems; and am involved in several
				          projects dealing with high-dimensional (<i>n << p</i>) and big-data problems in human genetics, statistical chemistry and climate science.
